Mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani tallan shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka mai dauke da labaran cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafafen yada labarai na Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana a ranar Laraba game da biyan kudin da ake samu a jaridar China Daily a De Moine Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa - bayan da ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben 'yan majalisar dattijai na Amurka a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, kasar Sin ta yi watsi da zargin.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna wa Reuters cewa jami'an tsaro na Amurka sun yi sabon mataki a yakin neman matsin lamba da Washington ke yi kan kasar Sin.
Duk da yake al'ada ce gwamnatocin kasashen waje su buga tallace-tallace don inganta cinikayya, Beijing da Washington suna cikin yakin kasuwanci a halin yanzu inda suke daidaita harajin shigo da kayayyaki da juna.
Tallafin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya ya shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohin tarayya kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana na China da na Amurka sun tabbatar.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing na cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da 'yan kasuwa.
China, in ji Branstad a wani shafi a cikin jaridar De Moyne Register ta mako-mako, "yanzu ta ninka cin zarafin tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin jaridarmu mai 'yanci".
"A cikin lalata farfagandar, gwamnatin China ta yi amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da' yan jarida masu 'yanci ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace a cikin De Moyne Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a cikin kantin labarai na kusa da nan a Beijing, za ku iya samun iyakantaccen ra'ayi kuma ba za ku ga ainihin ma'anar ra'ayoyin da mutanen China ke da shi game da matsalar tattalin arzikin China ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
